Here are 3 beginner tips for using the Siser® Juliet™ High Definition Cutter (may also apply to other cutting machines)

1. Check and recalibrate your cut settings each time to make sure they are correct for the material you are cutting. With the Siser® Juliet™, you can do a test cut by pressing the little t-shirt icon on the machine screen. 

2. Don't forget to mirror your image or text when cutting Heat Transfer Vinyl, and flip your material shiny side down! In Leonardo Design Studio, there is a box to check the mirror option.

3. If cutting cardstock, peel back your mat instead of peeling off your paper. This prevents your cut out from curling and becoming warped.

Waffle Maker Cleaning Hack 🧇

4. Wipe and let dry before storing away

Viral Sheet Pan Lasagna 👨‍🍳

You NEED to add this to your weekly meal rotation! All the yummy lasagna goodness without the tedious layering. Leftovers the next day are even better!

Recipe adapted from #giadadelaurentiis

[Ingredients]
16 ounces lasagna noodles broken into 2-inch pieces
½ pound ground beef
½ pound Italian sausage
1 yellow onion diced
2 tablespoons minced garlic
24 ounces pasta sauce
2 teaspoons Italian seasonings salt to taste ground black pepper to taste
2 cups ricotta cheese
8 ounces spinach frozen but thawed and drained
2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese divided
2 cups grated Parmesan cheese divided

[Directions]
Preheat oven to 350. Bring a large pot of water to a boil and add in the lasagna noodles and cook until al dente. Strain and set aside.

In a large deep skillet, cook the ground beef, sausage, onion, and garlic over medium heat until browned. Drain off excess fat and return to the pan.

Stir in the pasta sauce, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper, and bring to a simmer for 10 minutes.

In a separate bowl, mix together the ricotta cheese, thawed and drained spinach, and some salt and pepper to taste and set aside.

Once the sauce is done, pour it into the bowl with the prepared pasta and mix it together. Then stir in 1 cup of mozzarella cheese and 1 cup of parmesan cheese.

Lightly spray a 13x18-inch (half sheet) sheet pan with nonstick cooking spray.  Pour all the lasagna mixture onto the baking sheet and spread evenly.  Dollop the ricotta mixture all over the top, then top with the remaining mozzarella and parmesan cheese.

Bake for 35-40 minutes or until the cheese is golden and bubbly. Let lasagna cool for 10 minutes before serving.

Enjoy! 😘

Ingredients:

3/4 cup of Greek yogurt
1/2 vegetable oil 
1 cup light brown sugar
1 cup white sugar
2 tsp vanilla extract 
2 cups all-purpose flour
2 tsp baking powder 
1/2 tsp salt
1 Tbsp ground cinnamon 
1/2 tsp nutmeg
3 cups grated carrots
1/4 cup chopped pecans (optional)

Cream Cheese Frosting 
8 oz cream cheese
1/4 cup unsalted butter 
3 cups powdered sugar 
1 tsp vanilla 

Directions:
Preheat oven to 350. Line cupcake tin with liners. Combine wet ingredients in a large bowl (eggs, yogurt, oil, sugars, vanilla). Stir until combined. In a separate bowl, combine dry ingredients and whisk to combine. Slowly add dry ingredients to the wet, stirring to combine. Fold in grated carrots and pecans (if using). Scoop into cupcake liners (3/4 full). Bake for 20 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Let cool before adding frosting.

Frosting:
Cream together cream cheese and butter until smooth. Add vanilla and powdered sugar and mix on high until smooth and creamy.

UPDATE on Luna 🐶

If you've been following along, I shared how our 11 year old corgi Luna was diagnosed with IVDD (Intervertebral Disc Disease). She quickly lost the ability to walk, move any of her limbs, and we had to physically carry her so she could relieve herself.

We are so grateful to have even a few more years with Luna. (Whoever it was, please DM me, let me buy you dinner at the very least!)

Pull Apart Chocolate Chip Christmas Tree 🎄 

2 cans refrigerated Crescent Rolls 
6 oz (from 8-oz package) cream cheese, softened
1/2 cup powdered sugar
1/2 cup semisweet chocolate chips

Directions:
Heat oven to 375°F. Line large cookie sheet with cooking parchment paper. Separate dough into 16 triangles. Use pizza cutter or sharp knife to cut each triangle in half lengthwise to get 32 triangles.

In a bowl, mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until blended. Spoon a teaspoon of the mixture on shortest side of each triangle; add a 1/2 teaspoon chocolate chips.

Roll up each crescent, starting at shortest side of triangle and rolling to opposite point. Place crescents next to each other in tree-shaped pattern on cookie sheet (work top to bottom)

Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until deep golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and enjoy!

Caprese Skewers: Valentine's Day Edition 🍅🌿❤️

You'll Need:
Olive Oil
Fresh Mozzarella
Grape Tomatoes
Fresh Basil
A heart mold

Preheat your oven ro 350. Spray your mold with olive oil and place mozzarella inside. Bake at 350 for 6-7 minutes. Cut your tomatoes in a diagonal then turn one side to create a heart. Add them to your skewer. Fold and roll up fresh basil to look like roses. Remove your Mozzarella and let cool, place in freezer for 10 minutes to set before gently popping them out of the mold. Add to your skewer and repeat the layers. Finish with a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil! 

Alternatively, you can skip the skewers and add to some pasta for a yummy pasta salad for you and your Valentine/ galentines!
